<p>
<p>A researcher observes that in his dataset with repeated measurements, the assumption of sphericity does not hold. He also notices that there is a lot of <em>missing data</em>. Which technique can best deal with violation of the assumption of sphericity and presence of missing data, and is therefore the most appropriate?</p>
</p>]]></text>
